"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-sport-olympics-weightlifting-drug-riddled-olympic-sport-nearly-never-made-paris-2024-3217562\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  Weightlifting has worked hard to clean up its image after facing expulsion from the Olympics following a string of doping offences  Luo Shifang, a 23-year-old fromChina, wonweightliftinggold in the women's 59kg division with a lift to spare on herOlympicdebut.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 306, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 178, \"end\": 181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\", \"score\": 0.5510313233847189, \"rank\": 0.814743708227352, \"text\": \"Luo\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\"}, {\"begin\": 182, \"end\": 189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shifang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shifang\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shifang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shifang\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both the snatch, and clean-and-jerk Olympic records fell in an astonishingly composed display in which she completed every lift attempted.\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her joy was augmented by the dethroning of the defending Olympic champion fromTokyo, Kuo Hsing-chun of Taiwan, who failed in her final attempt at a new Olympic clean-and-jerk record of 137kg.\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999760399156111, \"rank\": 2.3675894774673587e-05, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every micro success in the macro arm wrestle with China's neighbour over its contested sovereignty is diplomatic gold.\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 691, \"end\": 696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999373372100083, \"rank\": 2.8752891449601073e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The support in the packed audience was for the deposed queen, who ended the opening snatch session with a 2kg deficit to Luo after the debutant set the bar at 107kg.\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\", \"score\": 0.5510313233847189, \"rank\": 0.814743708227352, \"text\": \"Luo\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Luo made her first appearance in the clean-and-jerk half an hour into the session, opening at 129kg.\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 1028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A lift of 132kg allowed Canada's Maude Charron to draw level on a combined total of 236kg.\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1054, \"end\": 1060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.6079870955032581, \"rank\": 0.5883216636057914, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 1063, \"end\": 1076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maude_Charron\", \"score\": 0.9999981134355554, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maude Charron\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maude_Charron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maude_Charron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No problem.\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1132, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Out came Lou to set a new Olympic mark of a 134kg, which nobody else could match.\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1214, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What ceremony.\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1230, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can see why the International Olympic Committee (IOC) was so keen to retain weightlifting as an Olympic discipline despite a doping history that would make a Russian testing lab blush.\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1251, \"end\": 1288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1393, \"end\": 1400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9963987743948166, \"rank\": 0.003599355201366983, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bar is carried to the mat like some sacred implement and carefully set down.\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Next, a pair of assistants load it from each end and secure the plates.\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1573, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The snatch is pure heft in two stages, one to get the bar above your head, the second to raise it from a squatting position.\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1699, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first tranche among the 12 lifters are already stretched, knowing the pedigree of those coming behind.\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But can we trust what we are seeing?\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1843, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Weightlifting has been ever present at the Games since 1920 with women admitted for the first time in Sydney in 2000.\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1947, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9998675425552426, \"rank\": 0.0001324140284579941, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, with thesportbeset by habitual doping, it was struggling to retain its place on the roster in Paris.\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 2073, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2067, \"end\": 2072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.367217243244081e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Between 2008 and 2019 in all competitions, 565 weightlifters (none named in this article) were sanctioned for doping offences, leaving the sport on the precipice of Olympic expulsion.\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So entrenched had it become in Bulgaria and Russia both federations were banned from the Rio games in 2016 with wider reprisals feared after Tokyo.\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2291, \"end\": 2299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\", \"score\": 0.9937221020715064, \"rank\": 0.0058539161964688115, \"text\": \"Bulgaria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\"}, {\"begin\": 2304, \"end\": 2310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999706488698555, \"rank\": 2.3812497098724093e-05, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2349, \"end\": 2352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999974156708, \"rank\": 2.5841031072396278e-09, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2401, \"end\": 2406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8796086858901456, \"rank\": 0.1368691732951889, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The replacement of the disgraced International Wrestling Federation president Tamas Ajan with Iraqi official Mohammed Jalood in June 2022 and the wide-ranging reforms promised earned a stay of execution.\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2442, \"end\": 2476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_World_Wrestling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.2845655344897e-26, \"text\": \"International Wrestling Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_World_Wrestling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_World_Wrestling\"}, {\"begin\": 2487, \"end\": 2492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Tamas\", \"score\": 0.905047263079186, \"rank\": 0.06258968033965927, \"text\": \"Tamas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Tamas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Tamas\"}, {\"begin\": 2503, \"end\": 2508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ba'athist_Iraq\", \"score\": 0.8089747608673006, \"rank\": 0.23604497392606535, \"text\": \"Iraqi\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ba'athist_Iraq\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ba'athist_Iraq\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The quota of weightlifters at the games has shrunk to 120, less than half the 260 in Rio, but, depending on the success of the IWF in policing the cheats, there is the promise of an increase in Los Angeles 2028 and Brisbane 2032.\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2699, \"end\": 2702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999974156708, \"rank\": 2.5841031072396278e-09, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2741, \"end\": 2744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Weightlifting_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.389234578034744e-44, \"text\": \"IWF\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Weightlifting_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Weightlifting_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 2808, \"end\": 2824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles 2028\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So much of this sport is psychological, the participants parading behind the bar as if preparing to enter a cage housing a lion.\", \"from\": 2845, \"to\": 2973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At some point you have to cast aside doubt and cross that threshold.\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 3043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women in this category weigh 9st 4lbs.\", \"from\": 3044, \"to\": 3086, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They were all lifting more than twice their body weight in the lift-and-snatch.\", \"from\": 3087, \"to\": 3166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To add to the drama, the starting weight of the bar rises with the quality of the lifter.\", \"from\": 3168, \"to\": 3257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Failures are pretty much obvious immediately and frequently require evasive action to avoid injury.\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3357, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The power is in the legs and the shoulders, the former to lift the load, the latter to stabilise it.\", \"from\": 3358, \"to\": 3458, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The best tend to share a low centre of gravity.\", \"from\": 3460, \"to\": 3507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The tension intensifies at pinch points when outcomes rest on the capacity of quads already in distress to find the will to power the weight skywards.\", \"from\": 3508, \"to\": 3658, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The last of the contenders to appear in the snatch was crowd favourite Kuo, who speared the field with an initial lift of 104kg.\", \"from\": 3659, \"to\": 3787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3730, \"end\": 3733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong-Chih_Kuo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.734105885478895e-16, \"text\": \"Kuo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong-Chih_Kuo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong-Chih_Kuo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Luo answered with an Olympic record of 105kg, and made it look easy.\", \"from\": 3789, \"to\": 3857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This required a response.\", \"from\": 3859, \"to\": 3884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It took two attempts but Kuo stood stout and tall at least enough to make Luo go again.\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3910, \"end\": 3913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong-Chih_Kuo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.734105885478895e-16, \"text\": \"Kuo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong-Chih_Kuo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong-Chih_Kuo\"}, {\"begin\": 3959, \"end\": 3962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\", \"score\": 0.5510313233847189, \"rank\": 0.814743708227352, \"text\": \"Luo\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This she did with her third and final lift of the session raising the bar to a new record of 107kg.\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 4072, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Luo was supreme in the clean-and-jerk, requiring only two of the permitted three lifts to get the job done.\", \"from\": 4074, \"to\": 4181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The look on her face was contemptuous, and might have said: \\\"Really girls, you serious?\", \"from\": 4182, \"to\": 4269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do we have to go on with this?\\\"\", \"from\": 4270, \"to\": 4301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer came in a series of failed attempts as one by one her rivals collapsed, literally as well as metaphorically, under the weight of the challenge.\", \"from\": 4303, \"to\": 4457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Charron took silver with Kuo settling for bronze.\", \"from\": 4458, \"to\": 4507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4458, \"end\": 4465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_Friday\", \"score\": 0.9999999995461621, \"rank\": 3.5004243983049314e-10, \"text\": \"Charron\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_Friday\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_Friday\"}, {\"begin\": 4483, \"end\": 4486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong-Chih_Kuo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.734105885478895e-16, \"text\": \"Kuo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong-Chih_Kuo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong-Chih_Kuo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate  All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 4509, \"to\": 4566, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026